CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, pg. 3 reads: "In Their Easter Bonnets...and pretty frocks, too, these darling little girls paraded their spring finery at a fashion review at A. Leo Weil School. Some wore quilted skirts and toppers while others preferred sheer dressy frocks.  Left to right: ...Louise Hill..."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Louise Hill modeling light colored dress with knee socks and gloves, holding overcoat and acrylic box, standing on stage in A. Leo Weil School for Easter fashion show
